    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The decentralized practice and method by which individuals and groups create, manage, and share terms, names, etc. (called "tags") to annotate and categorize digital resources in an online "social" environment. This method is not necessarily collaborative because the effort is typically not organized, individuals are not actually working together or in concert, and standardization and common vocabulary are not employed.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000048379/Baca, Introduction to Metadata (2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De decentrale praktijk en methode waarbij individuen en groepen termen, namen, etc. (zogenaamde 'tags') creëren, beheren en delen om digitale bronnen in een online 'sociale' omgeving te markeren en te categoriseren. Deze methode komt niet per definitie door samenwerking tot stand, omdat de activiteit meestal niet is georganiseerd, de individuen niet echt samen of in onderling overleg werken en er geen sprake is van standaardisatie en een gemeenschappelijk jargon.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>個人或群體在一個線上「社會」環境中，各自創造、管理與分享詞彙、名稱等（稱為「標籤」），用來為數位資源做註解與分類。此方法不一定具合作性質，因為該行為通常沒有組織性，實際上並非由多人合作或協力完成，也沒有實行標準化與使用共通語彙。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
